snippet.textDisplay:
I’m so sad, that grown people feel the need to degrade children like that. Blue ivy is beautiful and her features are stunning! I know that black people is being treated different - don’t get me wrong.
But children in general are being talked down to, degraded and from an early age told that they are ugly if they don’t look like those “doll looking baby models” they show in the magazine (who are also getting retouched FYI).
I myself, is very light skinned with dark hair and have always been chubby. And that’s also looked down on - Because I wasn’t chubby in the right places, because I was too light or not the right kind of light, because i had too dark hair for my skin tone. Wtf people! Not everyone has the kar-Jenner money to make a new person out of what we got from our parents. Embrace your heritage! Embrace your natural beauty. Not everyone has to look the same. And it shouldn’t be this way - we shouldn’t have to make changes to feel beautiful and accepted. No matter race, gender, culture, religion, country, anything! And especially not children! ♥️
